{
  "diffMode": "binary",
  "formatName": "A-law Audio",
  "version": "1.15",
  "extensions": [
    ".alaw",
    ".al"
  ],
  "description": "A-law — an ITU-T G.711 logarithmic companding algorithm for 8-bit PCM encoding of voice audio, used in European PSTN telephony. A-law .alaw/.al files typically use the AU/SND container format starting with '.snd' (0x2E736E64), with the A-law encoding specified in the AU header encoding field (value 27 = G.711 A-law). Raw A-law is headerless 8-bit encoded audio at 8000 Hz (G.711 telephony standard), where each sample represents a 13-bit linear PCM value compressed to 8 bits using A-law companding. A-law is used in Europe and international circuits; μ-law (G.711 mu-law) is used in North America and Japan. Both produce 64 kbps at 8000 Hz mono.",
  "category": "Audio",
  "author": "WPFHexaEditor Team",
  "preferredEditor": "audio-viewer",
  "references": {
    "specifications": [
      "ITU-T G.711 — PCM of Voice Frequencies",
      "A-law logarithmic companding algorithm",
      "G.711 Telephony Codec Standard"
    ],
    "WebLinks": [
      "https://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-G.711/",
      "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G.711",
      "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A-law_algorithm"
    ]
  },
  "detection": {
    "signatures": [
      { "value": "2E736E64", "offset": 0, "label": "'.snd' AU/SND container header (may contain A-law)", "weight": 0.7 }
    ],
    "matchMode": "any",
    "MinimumScore": 0.7,
    "required": true,
    "Strength": "Medium",
    "EntropyHint": { "min": 3.0, "max": 5.5 },
    "validation": {
      "minFileSize": 24,
      "note": "A-law audio is typically stored in AU/SND container (0x2E736E64). Raw headerless A-law has no magic bytes. AU encoding field value 27 = G.711 A-law."
    }
  },
  "variables": {
    "sndMagic": "",
    "dataOffset": 0,
    "dataSize": 0,
    "encoding": 0,
    "sampleRate": 0,
    "channels": 0
  },
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "signature",
      "name": "AU/SND Magic",
      "offset": 0,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#FF6B6B",
      "opacity": 0.45,
      "description": "AU/SND file magic '.snd' (0x2E736E64). A-law audio is commonly stored in the AU container format (Sun/NeXT audio file format). The container's encoding field at offset 12 distinguishes A-law (27) from μ-law (1) and other encodings.",
      "storeAs": "sndMagic",
      "valueType": "ascii"
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "Data Offset",
      "offset": 4,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#4ECDC4",
      "opacity": 0.35,
      "description": "Byte offset from the start of the file to the audio data, stored as a 32-bit big-endian unsigned integer. Minimum 24 (the fixed AU header size). May be larger if annotation text follows the header.",
      "storeAs": "dataOffset",
      "valueType": "uint32",
      "endianness": "big"
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "Data Size",
      "offset": 8,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#95E1D3",
      "opacity": 0.35,
      "description": "Size of the audio data in bytes as a 32-bit big-endian unsigned integer. Value 0xFFFFFFFF (4294967295) means unknown length — used for streaming or piped audio where total size is not known at recording time.",
      "storeAs": "dataSize",
      "valueType": "uint32",
      "endianness": "big",
      "valueMap": {
        "4294967295": "Unknown data size (streaming/piped: 0xFFFFFFFF sentinel)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "Encoding",
      "offset": 12,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#FFE66D",
      "opacity": 0.35,
      "description": "Audio encoding format as a 32-bit big-endian unsigned integer. Value 27 = G.711 A-law (8-bit, 8000 Hz telephony). The A-law algorithm maps a 13-bit linear sample to 8 bits using a piecewise logarithmic compression curve defined in ITU-T G.711.",
      "storeAs": "encoding",
      "valueType": "uint32",
      "endianness": "big",
      "valueMap": {
        "1": "μ-law (G.711 mu-law, North America/Japan)",
        "2": "8-bit linear PCM",
        "3": "16-bit linear PCM",
        "27": "A-law (G.711 A-law, Europe/international PSTN)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "Sample Rate",
      "offset": 16,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#C7CEEA",
      "opacity": 0.30,
      "description": "Sample rate in Hz as a 32-bit big-endian unsigned integer. For G.711 A-law telephony this is always 8000 Hz (G.711 standard narrowband). Wideband G.711.1 uses 16000 Hz.",
      "storeAs": "sampleRate",
      "valueType": "uint32",
      "endianness": "big",
      "valueMap": {
        "8000": "8000 Hz — G.711 standard narrowband telephony",
        "16000": "16000 Hz — G.711.1 wideband extension"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "Channels",
      "offset": 20,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#B8B8FF",
      "opacity": 0.25,
      "description": "Number of audio channels as a 32-bit big-endian unsigned integer. G.711 A-law telephony is always mono (1 channel). Stereo (2 channels) is non-standard for G.711.",
      "storeAs": "channels",
      "valueType": "uint32",
      "endianness": "big"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "Encoding",
      "variable": "encoding",
      "description": "AU encoding: 27 = G.711 A-law, 1 = G.711 μ-law"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "Sample Rate",
      "variable": "sampleRate",
      "description": "Sample rate in Hz (8000 Hz for G.711 telephony)"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "Channels",
      "variable": "channels",
      "description": "Channel count (1 = mono for G.711)"
    }
  ],
  "assertions": [
    {
      "name": "AU magic valid",
      "expression": "sndMagic == '.snd'",
      "severity": "error",
      "message": "A-law audio in AU container must start with '.snd' (0x2E736E64)"
    },
    {
      "name": "Encoding is A-law",
      "expression": "encoding == 27",
      "severity": "info",
      "message": "Encoding field is not 27 (G.711 A-law) — may be a different AU encoding"
    }
  ],
  "inspector": {
    "badge": "encoding",
    "primaryField": "sampleRate",
    "showQualityScore": true,
    "groups": [
      {
        "title": "AU/SND Header",
        "icon": "\uE71B",
        "fields": ["sndMagic", "dataOffset", "dataSize"]
      },
      {
        "title": "A-law Encoding",
        "icon": "\uE767",
        "fields": ["encoding", "sampleRate", "channels"]
      }
    ]
  },
  "exportTemplates": [
    {
      "name": "A-law AU Header (JSON)",
      "format": "json",
      "fields": ["sndMagic", "dataOffset", "dataSize", "encoding", "sampleRate", "channels"]
    }
  ],
  "forensic": {
    "category": "audio",
    "riskLevel": "low",
    "suspiciousPatterns": []
  },
  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "A-law G.711 audio: AU/SND container '.snd'(4B) + dataOffset(4,BE) + dataSize(4,BE,0xFFFFFFFF=streaming) + encoding(4,BE: 27=A-law/1=μ-law) + sampleRate(4,BE,=8000) + channels(4,BE,=1). Raw headerless A-law: 8-bit samples at 8000 Hz, 64 kbps. A-law companding maps 13-bit linear PCM to 8 bits. European PSTN standard. μ-law is the North American/Japanese equivalent. Both are defined in ITU-T G.711. Conversion: A-law 0x55-XOR scrambling applied to each sample.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Verify '.snd' at offset 0 (2E 73 6E 64) — confirms AU container",
      "Read encoding at offset 12 (BE uint32): 27 = A-law, 1 = μ-law, 3 = 16-bit PCM",
      "Read sample rate at offset 16: should be 8000 Hz for G.711 telephony",
      "Data starts at dataOffset (typically 24): raw 8-bit A-law samples"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    "Audacity (with G.711 A-law plugin)",
    "FFmpeg (pcm_alaw codec)",
    "SoX (Sound eXchange)",
    "Asterisk PBX",
    "VLC media player"
  ],
  "formatRelationships": {
    "category": "Audio",
    "extensions": [".alaw", ".al"],
    "relatedFormats": ["ULAW", "AU", "WAV"],
    "note": "A-law and μ-law are the two G.711 companding variants. A-law is used in European E1 circuits; μ-law in North American T1 circuits. Both produce 8-bit, 64 kbps, 8000 Hz mono audio. A-law has slightly better dynamic range for low-level signals."
  },
  "MimeTypes": [
